1. Installation
-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

Add the dependency to your Cargo.toml:

    [dependencies]
    librjss = { git = "https://github.com/mroczect/librjss.git" }

Or use a specific version / tag as needed.

-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
2. Quick start – CLI binary
-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

A minimal CLI binary is included (src/bin/cli_auth.rs). Build and run
with environment variables:

    export JSS_BASE_URL=https://app.juragansejati.biz.id
    export JSS_EMAIL=user@example.com
    export JSS_PASSWORD=password
    export JSS_INSECURE_SSL=false          # set true only for dev

    cargo run --bin cli_auth

The CLI authenticates, prints session info, and performs a test request
to /api/method/frappe.auth.get_logged_user.

For token authentication, set JSS_TOKEN_API_KEY and JSS_TOKEN_API_SECRET
instead of email/password.

-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
3. Project layout
-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

src/
  api/
    auth/
      endpoints.rs         AuthEndpoints trait (URL builders)
      mod.rs
    mod.rs

  bin/
    cli_auth.rs            CLI login tool

  client/
    auth/
      app_parser.rs         Fetch /app, extract CSRF and frappe.boot
      http_helpers.rs       Auth header application, URL joining, backoff
      login.rs              Session login logic
      logout.rs             Session logout
      session.rs            Session maintenance (ensure_session)
      token.rs              Token‑mode session setup
      mod.rs
    methods/
      delete.rs             authenticated_delete
      get.rs                authenticated_get
      post.rs               authenticated_post
      put.rs                authenticated_put
      mod.rs
    file.rs                 Upload & download files (new)
    report.rs               Report execution builder (new)
    resource.rs             Doctype CRUD & listing builder (new)
    mod.rs                  RjssClient struct and core methods

  handler/
    config/
      auth_mode.rs          AuthMode enum
      client_config.rs      ClientConfig struct
      validation.rs         Config validation
      mod.rs
    env.rs                  Re‑exports for convenience
    error.rs                JssError enum (extended in 1.2.0)
    types/
      boot.rs               FrappeBoot, BootUser, permissions, reports
      login.rs              LoginApiResponse, LoginApiMessage
      session.rs            SessionInfo
      user_info.rs          UserInfo, UserInfoMessage
      mod.rs
    mod.rs

  lib.rs                    Crate root, public re‑exports

examples/
  jss_mock_server.rs        Full offline mock of a JSS server

tests/
  api_auth_tests.rs         URL builder tests
  client_tests.rs           Integration tests against mock server
  env_tests.rs              Config validation tests
  error_tests.rs            Error type tests
  file_tests.rs             File handling tests
  report_tests.rs           Report execution tests
  resource_tests.rs         Resource CRUD tests
  types_tests.rs            Deserialisation tests

.github/
  workflows/
    ci.yml                  CI pipeline

-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
4. Core concepts
-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

RjssClient
----------
Central client holding configuration, HTTP client, session, and
credentials. Public API (full list):

  new(config) -> Result<Self, JssError>
  authenticate() -> Result<(), JssError>
  logout() -> Result<(), JssError>
  ensure_session() -> Result<(), JssError>
  session_info() -> Option<&SessionInfo>
  boot() -> Option<&FrappeBoot>          // new
  base_url() -> &Url
  trace_id() -> &str
  authenticated_get(path) -> Result<String, JssError>
  authenticated_post(path, json) -> Result<String, JssError>
  authenticated_put(path, json) -> Result<String, JssError>
  authenticated_delete(path) -> Result<String, JssError>

  // File operations (new)
  upload_file(file_name, file_content, doctype, docname, fieldname)
      -> Result<String, JssError>
  download_file(file_url) -> Result<Vec<u8>, JssError>
  download_file_to_path(file_url, save_path) -> Result<(), JssError>

  // Report builder (new)
  report(name) -> ReportBuilder

  // Doctype/resource builder (new)
  doctype(name) -> ResourceBuilder
  get_doc(doctype, name) -> Result<String, JssError>
  create_doc(doctype, &data) -> Result<String, JssError>
  update_doc(doctype, name, &data) -> Result<String, JssError>
  delete_doc(doctype, name) -> Result<String, JssError>
  call_method(method, args) -> Result<String, JssError>

AuthMode (enum)
-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - --
  Session { email: SecretString, password: SecretString }
  Token   { api_key: String, api_secret: SecretString }

ClientConfig
------------
  base_url: Url
  auth_mode: AuthMode
  expected_sitename: Option<String>
  required_roles: Vec<String>
  timeout_secs: u64           (default 30)
  max_retries: u32            (default 3)
  user_agent: String
  insecure_ssl: bool          (default false)
  Method: validate() -> Result<(), JssError>

JssError (enum) – version 1.2.0 extended
-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - ------------
  Config(String)
  Validation(String)
  Network(reqwest::Error)
  Http { status, body }
  ApiError { exc_type, message, status }      // new
  Auth(String)
  Csrf(String)
  Permission(String)
  SitenameMismatch { expected, actual }
  NotAuthenticated
  RateLimited { retry_after: Option<u64> }    // changed
  Parse(String)
  Expired
  Cancelled
  FileOperation(String)                       // new
  Internal(String)                            // new

New method: from_api_response(status, body) – parses Frappe JSON
errors; status_code() maps any variant to an HTTP status.

SessionInfo
-----------
  sid: SecretString
  csrf_token: SecretString
  full_name: Option<String>
  sitename: String
  roles: Vec<String>

FrappeBoot (extended)
-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - --------
Deserialised from the /app dashboard. Now includes:

  user: BootUser (with name, email, full_name, roles, user_type,
        permissions, and can_select/can_create/can_write/can_read/
        can_submit/can_cancel/can_delete/can_get_report,
        all_reports)
  sitename, csrf_token, sysdefaults
  app_logo_url, home_page
  allow_modules
  can_select, can_create, can_write, can_read, can_submit,
  can_cancel, can_delete, can_get_report (global)
  all_reports: HashMap<String, ReportMeta>
  module_wise_workspaces
  dashboards: Vec<DashboardMeta>
  single_types, calendars, treeviews
  module_app, app_data

BootUser also contains the same permission lists and all_reports.

ReportMeta, DashboardMeta, AppData, SysDefaults are new supporting
structs.

-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
5. New in version 1.2.0
-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

File Handling
  - upload_file: multipart upload to /api/method/upload_file.
  - download_file: download raw bytes from a file URL.
  - download_file_to_path: save directly to disk.

Report Execution
  - client.report("Report Name") returns a ReportBuilder.
  - add_filter("field", "value") for filtering.
  - run_raw() -> JSON string, run::<T>() -> deserialized.

Doctype/Resource CRUD
  - client.doctype("ToDo") returns a ResourceBuilder with filter(),
    fields(), order_by(), limit(), limit_start().
  - execute_raw(), execute::<T>() for a single page.
  - all::<T>() auto‑paginates and collects every record.
  - Direct methods: get_doc, create_doc, update_doc, delete_doc.
  - call_method: call any whitelisted Frappe server method.

Boot Data Exposure
  - After authentication, FrappeBoot is stored and accessible via
    client.boot().
  - All permission vectors and reports are now available.

Enhanced Error Model
  - ApiError variant captures Frappe’s exc_type and exc message.
  - RateLimited now carries optional Retry-After duration.
  - New FileOperation and Internal variants.
  - from_api_response() and status_code() helper methods.

Better Retry & Rate Limit Handling
  - All methods now read response body on server errors.
  - Login extracts Retry-After header.
  - Internal helpers extract_retry_after and classify_response
    added for future retry strategies.

Breaking Changes
  - JssError::RateLimited is now RateLimited { retry_after }.
  - JssError enum has three new variants (ApiError, FileOperation,
    Internal); exhaustive matches must be updated.
  - Server errors that were previously JssError::Http with empty
    body now may return JssError::ApiError when the body contains
    a valid Frappe JSON error.

-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
6. Usage examples
-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

All examples assume you have created and authenticated a client.

6.1 Basic authenticated request

    let body = client.authenticated_get("/api/resource/ToDo").await?;
    println!("{}", body);

    let response = client
        .authenticated_post("/api/resource/ToDo",
            r#"{"description":"test"}"#)
        .await?;

6.2 File upload

    let result = client
        .upload_file("photo.png", image_bytes,
                      "Customer", "CUST-001", "image")
        .await?;
    // result is JSON with file_url

6.3 File download

    let bytes = client.download_file("/files/photo.png").await?;
    std::fs::write("local.png", &bytes)?;

    // or
    client.download_file_to_path("/files/photo.png",
                                 Path::new("local.png")).await?;

6.4 Report

    let report_data: serde_json::Value = client
        .report("Sales Analytics")
        .add_filter("from_date", "2026-01-01")
        .add_filter("to_date", "2026-06-30")
        .run()
        .await?;

    // raw string
    let raw = client.report("Balance Sheet").run_raw().await?;

6.5 Doctype listing with filters and pagination

    let list: serde_json::Value = client
        .doctype("ToDo")
        .filter("status", "=", "Open")
        .fields(vec!["name", "description", "date"])
        .order_by("creation desc")
        .limit(50)
        .execute()
        .await?;

    // All records, auto‑paginated
    let all_todos: Vec<ToDoStruct> = client
        .doctype("ToDo")
        .filter("status", "=", "Cancelled")
        .all()
        .await?;

6.6 Single document CRUD

    let doc = client.get_doc("Customer", "CUST-001").await?;

    #[derive(Serialize)]
    struct NewCustomer {
        customer_name: String,
        customer_group: String,
    }
    let new_cust = NewCustomer { ... };
    let result = client.create_doc("Customer", &new_cust).await?;

    let result = client.update_doc("Customer", "CUST-001",
                                     &update_data).await?;

    let result = client.delete_doc("Customer", "OLD-CUST").await?;

6.7 Call a custom method

    use std::collections::HashMap;
    let mut args = HashMap::new();
    args.insert("doctype".into(), "Sales Invoice".into());
    args.insert("docname".into(), "SINV-0001".into());
    let result = client.call_method("frappe.email.send", Some(args)).await?;

6.8 Error handling

    match client.authenticated_get("/api/resource/ToDo").await {
        Err(JssError::ApiError { exc_type, message, status }) => {
            eprintln!("API error [{exc_type}]: {message} (HTTP {status})");
        }
        Err(JssError::RateLimited { retry_after }) => {
            eprintln!("Rate limited, retry after {:?}", retry_after);
        }
        other => { /* handle other errors */ }
    }

    // Convert any error to HTTP status code
    let status = some_error.status_code();

-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
7. Environment variables (CLI)
-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

These are used by cli_auth and can be used as a reference for your
own applications.

JSS_BASE_URL            Required. Base URL of the JSS instance.
JSS_EMAIL               Required for session auth.
JSS_PASSWORD            Required for session auth.
JSS_TOKEN_API_KEY       Required for token auth (ignored if session
                        variables are set).
JSS_TOKEN_API_SECRET    Required for token auth.
JSS_EXPECTED_SITENAME   Optional. If set, login verifies the sitename
                        in frappe.boot matches.
JSS_REQUIRED_ROLES      Optional. Comma‑separated roles the user must
                        possess.
JSS_TIMEOUT_SECS        Optional. Request timeout in seconds (default 30).
JSS_MAX_RETRIES         Optional. Maximum retry attempts (default 3).
JSS_USER_AGENT          Optional. Custom User‑Agent header.
JSS_INSECURE_SSL        Optional. Accept invalid TLS certificates
                        (true/false, default false).

-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
8. Mock server for development
-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

A full mock server is provided in examples/jss_mock_server.rs. It
replicates the exact behaviour of a JSS production instance: login
response, cookie setting, /app dashboard with frappe.boot,
get_logged_user, logout, and the missing CSRF endpoint (returns 417).

Start the mock server:

    cargo run --example jss_mock_server

It listens on http://127.0.0.1:8080.

Set environment variables accordingly:

    export JSS_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080
    export JSS_EMAIL=dev@example.com
    export JSS_PASSWORD=password123
    export JSS_INSECURE_SSL=true

Then run the CLI or integration tests. The library does not know the
difference between mock and production.

-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
9. Testing
-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

Unit tests (no server required):

    cargo test --lib

Integration tests require the mock server to be running:

    (terminal 1)  cargo run --example jss_mock_server
    (terminal 2)  JSS_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8080 \
                  JSS_EMAIL=dev@example.com \
                  JSS_PASSWORD=password123 \
                  JSS_INSECURE_SSL=true \
                  cargo test --test client_tests

For the new test suites:

    cargo test --test file_tests
    cargo test --test report_tests
    cargo test --test resource_tests

Run all tests after starting the mock server:

    cargo test --workspace

-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -
10. CI pipeline
-  - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

Located at .github/workflows/ci.yml. On every push or pull request
to master:

    - Check formatting (rustfmt)
    - Lint (clippy -D warnings)
    - Compile check (cargo check --workspace)
    - Run unit tests (cargo test --lib)
    - Start mock server, run integration tests
    - Build release binary (cargo build --release)
    - Upload release artifact (cli_auth)

